The White House Office of the Press Secretary has announced the unveiling of the Childhood Obesity Task Force's action plan, "Solving the Problem of Childhood Obesity Within a Generation." The goal of the plan is to reduce childhood obesity rates to 5 percent by 2030. The report includes 70 recommendations, including improving prenatal care, supporting breastfeeding, limiting screen time, providing nutritious food in child care settings, empowering parents with actionable nutritional messages, improving school lunches and nutrition education, increasing access to healthy and affordable food, promoting physical activity in schools and communities, and partnering with the private sector. Federal agencies will be implementing various recommendations, and funds will be made available to support obesity prevention and physical education programs. Cabinet members and Administration officials will also be holding events across the country to highlight their efforts in addressing childhood obesity.